Its well known that folks become far-sighted (short-armed 8-) with age.
Its well known that close-work leads to near-sightedness, or you might
just
be born with it.  So you might think they would cross over at some point

--leading to retrograde acuity.  I'm nearing 40 and it hasn't happened
yet,
though I haven't asked my optometrist to plot the second derivative of
my resolution.
Its encouraging to find that Neil is benefitting from age.  He chose
better ancestors
in that respect than me.

